LOW|internal/reconcile/merge.go:390|mergeVerification keeps only the winning verdict block's Notes and ChallengeSurvived. When a confirmed member wins over a refuted sibling, the refuted sibling's reasoning is discarded entirely; skeptic names are unioned for provenance but the minority verdict's reasoning is lost, so a human auditing why a confirmed cluster also had a refutation cannot see it. The doc acknowledges only the winner's fields are kept, but this is a deliberate audit-data loss worth a conscious decision.|Either append losing-member notes to the chosen Notes (prefixed with verdict, e.g. "[refuted by sk1] disproved A") or explicitly document in the struct/contract that minority-verdict reasoning is intentionally dropped at cluster-merge. Verify by merging confirmed+refuted and asserting the note is preserved or the loss is documented.|maintainability|15|internal/reconcile/merge.go:370-392|claude
